          </svg>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="people">
      <p class="s-label reveal">For whom and why</p>
      <div class="people-header reveal">
        <h2 class="people-heading">Technology is not the point. People are.</h2>
        <p class="people-sub">
          <em>Ara</em> from Turkmen language translated as a "space in between", or
          medium as abstract. That's goal of Ara to be abstract and invisible without
          pointing out to any technology or protocol. Instead, it's pointing on alignment
          of four groups of people who build, run, and semantically align the Web
          for the benefit of all.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="people-grid reveal">
        <div class="person">
          <div class="person-role-row">
            <p class="person-role">Users</p>
            <span class="person-bust person-bust-user" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 92" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <ellipse cx="40" cy="28" rx="18" ry="19" fill="#c8a87a"
                ></ellipse>
                <path d="M22 24 Q 24 8 40 6 Q 56 8 58 24" fill="#1a1408"></path>
                <ellipse cx="33" cy="27" rx="3" ry="4" fill="#1a1408"></ellipse>
                <ellipse cx="47" cy="27" rx="3" ry="4" fill="#1a1408"></ellipse>
                <rect x="34" y="44" width="12" height="10" rx="3" fill="#b89060"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="18" y="52" width="44" height="28" rx="8" fill="#2a3545"
                ></rect>
                <path d="M18 58 Q 40 70 62 58 L 62 80 L 18 80 Z" fill="#242e3e"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="person-title">You are king of computer</h3>
          <p class="person-desc">
            Your device adapts to you and work on your terms
            <br /><i
              >user sama &ndash; thats how <strong>you</strong> are called by AI minions</i
            >
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="person">
          <div class="person-role-row">
            <p class="person-role">Designers</p>
            <span class="person-bust person-bust-designer" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 92" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <ellipse cx="40" cy="29" rx="17" ry="18" fill="#e8c49a"
                ></ellipse>
                <path
                  d="M22 24 Q 25 11 40 9 Q 55 11 58 24 Q 53 15 40 15 Q 27 15 22 24"
                  fill="#432918"></path>
                <ellipse cx="33" cy="29" rx="2.8" ry="3.6" fill="#2a1a10"
                ></ellipse>
                <ellipse cx="47" cy="29" rx="2.8" ry="3.6" fill="#2a1a10"
                ></ellipse>
                <rect x="34" y="46" width="12" height="9" rx="3" fill="#d4a87a"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="18" y="54" width="44" height="26" rx="8" fill="#5b2f52"
                ></rect>
                <path d="M18 62 Q 40 52 62 62 L 62 80 L 18 80 Z" fill="#47213f"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="person-title">Experiment and go viral</h3>
          <p class="person-desc">
            Build interfaces as an Art. Get funds and go viral by users who
            appreciate your work and use it as lego brick.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="person">
          <div class="person-role-row">
            <p class="person-role">Open Source Developers</p>
            <span class="person-bust person-bust-dev" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 92" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <ellipse cx="40" cy="28" rx="17" ry="18" fill="#d6b182"
                ></ellipse>
                <path d="M22 25 Q 25 8 40 7 Q 55 8 58 25" fill="#1a1408"></path>
                <rect
                  x="28"
                  y="25"
                  width="24"
                  height="10"
                  rx="5"
                  fill="none"
                  stroke="#3a4a5a"
                  stroke-width="3"></rect>
                <ellipse cx="34" cy="30" rx="2.5" ry="3.5" fill="#1a1408"
                ></ellipse>
                <ellipse cx="46" cy="30" rx="2.5" ry="3.5" fill="#1a1408"
                ></ellipse>
                <rect x="34" y="45" width="12" height="9" rx="3" fill="#bc9668"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="18" y="54" width="44" height="26" rx="8" fill="#2a3a4a"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="26" y="61" width="28" height="7" rx="3" fill="#1f2c3b"
                ></rect>
                <rect x="56" y="60" width="8" height="10" rx="2" fill="#78c878"
                ></rect>
              </svg>
            </span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="person-title">Build the backbone, set the protocols</h3>
          <p class="person-desc">
            No worry about sophisticated UI. Make your source code as a craft.
            Design data models to connect with other apps and set protocol
            standard without consortiums.

            <br /><br />
            Get funds and go viral by users who appreciate your work and use it as
            lego brick.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="person">
          <p class="person-role">Node Operators</p>
          <h3 class="person-title">Find the best path between all three</h3>
          <p class="person-desc">
            You are the connective tissue. Your work routes meaning through the
            network, keeping users, designers, and developers in alignment.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="pilot" class="pilot-section">
      <p class="s-label reveal">Now</p>
      <div class="pilot-inner">
        <div class="reveal">
          <div class="pilot-tag">Pilot version</div>
          <h2 class="pilot-heading">Join us.</h2>
          <p class="pilot-body">
            Before making computers communicate for malleable software, we need
            to solve another problem: open-source is not sustainable. Our
            current phase is solving that.
            <Link uri="https://cascadefund.org" focus asNewTab
              >Visit CascadeFund</Link
            >
          </p>
          <p class="pilot-body pilot-body-extra">
            CascadeFund is for those who care about open-source.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal reveal-d">
          <div class="pilot-roadmap">
            <article class="pilot-roadmap-item">
              <h3 class="pilot-roadmap-title">1. Whitepaper foundation</h3>
              <p class="pilot-roadmap-desc">
                Design and all code details are ready after
                <strong>3 years of experiment</strong>. Result is whitepaper.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="pilot-roadmap-item pilot-roadmap-item-current">
              <h3 class="pilot-roadmap-title">
                2. Pilot version: cascadefund
                <span class="pilot-current-badge">current</span>
              </h3>
              <p class="pilot-roadmap-desc">
                Pre-blockchain, pre-holographic. Onboard open-source developers
                and users to make the open-source ecosystem sustainable and
                user-centric.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="pilot-roadmap-item">
              <h3 class="pilot-roadmap-title">
                3. Local data project management
              </h3>
              <p class="pilot-roadmap-desc">
                Local data version for project management made from open-source
                with local AI. Onboarding the node operators on your browser.
              </p>
            </article>
            <article class="pilot-roadmap-item">
              <h3 class="pilot-roadmap-title">
                4. Recommendation engine and desktop shell
              </h3>
              <p class="pilot-roadmap-desc">
                Recommendation engine and desktop shell, onboarding designers.
              </p>
            </article>
            <p class="pilot-roadmap-note">
              More information on the <a href="/roadmap">roadmap page</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <footer
      class="mt-20 border-t border-neutral-200 pb-10 pt-10 text-center text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:border-white/10 dark:text-neutral-500"
      aria-label="Home page footer"
    >
      <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-500">
        © {companyInfo.copyrightYear} Ara Foundation.
      </p>
    </footer>
  </div>

  <script>
    // @ts-nocheck
    const revealElements = document.querySelectorAll(".ara-main .reveal");
    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        entries.forEach((entry) => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            entry.target.classList.add("visible");
            observer.unobserve(entry.target);
          }
        });
      },
      { threshold: 0.1 },
    );
    revealElements.forEach((element) => observer.observe(element));

    import { comics } from "@/data/comics";

    const overlay = document.getElementById("comicOverlay");
    const scroll = document.getElementById("comicScroll");
    const closeBtn = document.getElementById("comicCloseBtn");
    const cards = document.querySelectorAll("[data-comic-id]");
    let currentComicId = "";

    const openComic = (id = "") => {
      const comic = comics[id];
      if (!comic || !overlay || !scroll) return;
      currentComicId = id;
      const panelsHtml = comic.panels
        .map(
          (panel, index) => `
        <div class="comic-panel ${panel.bg}">
          <div class="panel-illustration">${panel.html}</div>
          <div class="panel-text">
            <p class="panel-caption">${panel.caption}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      `,
        )
        .join("");
      const nextButtonHtml =
        id === "teacher"
          ? `<div class="comic-footer-nav show-next" style="display:flex;justify-content:center;padding:1.25rem 1.2rem 1.6rem;background:#000;">
               <button class="comic-next-btn" id="comicNextBtn" type="button" style="appearance:none;border:1px solid #4bb18b;background:#1f6f55;color:#e7fff5;font-family:'DM Mono',monospace;font-size:0.72rem;letter-spacing:0.11em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:0.75rem 1.3rem;cursor:pointer;">
                 Next Example
               </button>
             </div>`
          : "";
      scroll.innerHTML = panelsHtml + nextButtonHtml;
      scroll.scrollTop = 0;
      overlay.classList.add("open");
      document.body.style.overflow = "hidden";

      const nextBtn = document.getElementById("comicNextBtn");
      nextBtn?.addEventListener("click", () => {
        if (currentComicId !== "teacher") return;
        const nextComicId = comics.student ? "student" : "programmer";
        openComic(nextComicId);
      });
    };

    const closeComic = () => {
      if (!overlay) return;
      overlay.classList.remove("open");
      currentComicId = "";
      document.body.style.overflow = "";
    };

    cards.forEach((card) => {
      card.addEventListener("click", () => {
        const comicId = card.getAttribute("data-comic-id");
        if (comicId) {
          openComic(comicId);
        }
      });
    });

    closeBtn?.addEventListener("click", closeComic);
    document.addEventListener("keydown", (event) => {
      if (event.key === "Escape") {
        closeComic();
      }
    });
  </script>
</MinimalDarkLayout>

<style>
  @import url("https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Playfair+Display:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400&family=DM+Mono:wght@300;400&family=Source+Serif+4:ital,opsz,wght@0,8..60,300;0,8..60,400;1,8..60,300&display=swap");

  .ara-main {
    --bg: #0d0d0d;
    --bg2: #141414;
    --bg3: #1a1a1a;
    --line: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.07);
    --line2: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.12);
    --text: #e8e2d8;
    --dim: #807a70;
    --dimmer: #4a4540;
    --accent: #d4824a;
    --gold: #c9a84c;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: var(--text);
    font-family: "Source Serif 4", Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 18px;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .ara-main * {
    box-sizing: border-box;
  }

  .ara-main a {
    color: inherit;
  }

  .ara-main .hero {
    min-height: 50vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: center;
    padding: 10rem 4rem 6rem;
    position: relative;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
  }

